| ''Legend of Mana'' features different gameplay than its predecessors. The locations of the game's world are represented on a map by artifacts placed by the player, with different artifact placements allowing him or her to obtain different items. The game features temporary sidekick characters that the player can recruit, breed or build, and a weapon and armor creation and tempering system. It also features a story with many diverging subplots.<ref name="GS-LoM">{{cite web| url=http://www.gamespot.com/ps/rpg/legendofmanathe/review.html| title=Legend of Mana Full Review| accessdate=2007-06-15| author=Vestal, Andrew| date=2000-06-07| work=[[GameSpot]]| publisher=[[CNET Networks]]}}</ref> Critical reaction was mixed at the dramatic shift in gameplay and story structure from ''[[Secret of Mana]]''.<ref name="IGN-LoM">{{cite web| url=http://psx.ign.com/articles/162/162141p1.html| title=Legend of Mana Full Review| accessdate=2008-02-15| author=IGN Staff| date=2000-06-06| work=[[IGN]]| publisher=[[IGN Entertainment]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.rpgamer.com/games/sd/sd4/reviews/sd4strev1.html| title=Different is Good| accessdate=2008-02-16| author=Andrew P. Bilyk| date=2000-06-01| work=[[RPGamer]]| publisher=The Crave Gaming Channel}}</ref>
